<headline>Winter Storm Watch issued December 17 at 1:54PM MST until December 19 at 11:00AM MST by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH
SUNDAY MORNING FOR ELEVATIONS ABOVE 4500 FEET...
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible for elevations above 4500 feet. Total
snow accumulations up to 8 inches possible. Winds could gust as
high as 60 mph.
* WHERE...Southern Rocky Mountain Front.
* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Sunday morning.
* IMPACTS...Whiteout conditions are possible and may make travel
treacherous and potentially life-threatening. Plan on slippery
road conditions. Strong winds could cause extensive damage to
trees and power lines.</description>
<instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.</instruction>
